## Decision records

Architecture decisions live in `{{ADR_DIR}}/`. Index: `{{ADR_DIR}}/README.md`.
ADRs are proposed automatically during plan close-out (the implementation
session decides per a confidence rule; see `/plan` Phase 4). For ad-hoc
decisions outside a plan, write `{{ADR_DIR}}/NNNN-slug.md` directly with
status `proposed`. Past decisions are append-only — to change one, write
a new ADR that supersedes it.

## Workflow

Two slash commands only:

- `/plan <task>` — non-trivial change. Read-only planning, durable
  artifact in `docs/plans/`, then implementation, then inline
  close-out (verify, auto-ADR, mark completed, memory consolidation).
- `/install-on <path>` — install or re-install aims (idempotent).

Everything else (bug-fix patches, refactors with obvious scope,
mechanical edits, ad-hoc questions): just do the work inline.

## Models policy

- Planning + plan close-out → **Opus** (auto via slash command frontmatter).
- Implementation → any model — switch with `/model <name>` per preference.

## Hooks

Mode: `{{HOOK_MODE}}` (configured at `.claude/aims-mode`). Change with:
```
echo nudge > .claude/aims-mode    # warn only
echo block > .claude/aims-mode    # block source edits without active plan
```
The planning lock (`.claude/.planning-lock`) always blocks edits regardless
of mode — this is what makes `/plan` actually read-only.

## Memory tree

The repo carries a navigable memory layer under `docs/memory/` (see
`docs/adr/0007-tree-based-memory-with-auto-maintenance.md` for the
full design). It is a NAVIGATOR over `CLAUDE.md`, ADRs, plans, and
external memory — never a copy of them.

- The tree is bootstrapped by `/install-on` (Phase 5) — fresh
  install runs a cold-start scan; re-install only augments
  (adds nodes for newly-discovered code areas; never overwrites
  existing node bodies).
- The `PostToolUse` marker hook flips affected leaves to
  `dirty: true` after every Edit/Write. The `Stop` hook
  consolidates dirty leaves in-band (ADR-0009), but only when the
  throttle trips (5 dirty leaves OR 30 min since last
  consolidation). `SessionEnd` runs the same consolidation
  un-throttled if the CLI is actually closed.
- Plan close-out (inline at end of `/plan` implementation) also
  forces consolidation of nodes touched by the plan.
- To browse the tree manually: `cat docs/memory/README.md`, then any
  leaf under `docs/memory/<tag>/<name>.md`.

Project conventions (build/test, models, hooks, layout) stay in
CLAUDE.md; the tree references them via `claude_md_refs:`.
